reviews.review_text: Montana Dead The only time GD played Montana.  According to audience accounts as well as the local newspaper, someone from the audience threw an empty plastic pitcher and hit Bob Weir as they came on stage for the encore.  Sadly, that may be a reason why they never played in Montana again (though Weir has played Missoula in the form of Ratdog and Wolf Bros. a few times).  Show sounds good and what an excellent recording!  Thanks for loading!

Wow Coulbe one of THE best Dead Shows of all time!!   Especially unknown ones.  Thanks and thanks for the info.
CO dead head all in the family!

Might as well I read so many reviews of all these different shows. Those were great years. I couldn’t tell you how many shows I’ve been to. I always say if you remember them, you probably weren’t there. You can complain about sound you can complain about whether you can complain about anything. 
Ever since I started listening to the dead, which I believe was in the backseat of my father‘s car in the driveway because it was the only vehicle that had an eight track player. It was live dead. Everybody complains about sound and I’ve had a fight so much hissduring so many shows I’ve listened to complain. Just enjoy as far as Ratings go the hell with it
